cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel deep-based framework for action recognition, which is a task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of fusion networks, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the use of more precise features and reducing asynchrony, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
